\par \pard\plain \s10\li120\sl-240 \f25\fs20\lang1033 
Net Gomuku is in many ways similar to an advanced form of tic-tac-toe.  It is played on a 15 x 15 grid.  The object of the game is to get five of your pegs in a row either horizontally, vertically, or diagonally while preventing your opponent from doing t
he same thing.
\par \pard\plain \li120\sb80\sl-240 \f25\fs20\lang1033 The players take turns putting their pegs on the board.  A player can place a peg into any open hole.  Once a peg is placed in a hole it can not be moved.
\par The strategy is to place the pegs so you have multiple ways to get five in a row.  Four consecutive peg in a row with a free hole on each end already represents a win.
\par \pard\plain \s254\li120\sb280\sa120\sl-320 \b\f25\lang1033 \{bml board.bmp\}\page {\fs18\up6 ${\footnote \pard\plain \s245\li120\sb80\sl-240 \f25\fs20\lang1033 {\fs18\up6 $} Playing Against the Computer}} {\fs18\up6 #{\footnote \pard\plain 
