}} Playing Over the Network
\par \pard\plain \s10\li120\sl-240 \f25\fs20\lang1033 The main feature of {\b Net Gomuku} is playing an opponent over the network like the {\b Hearts} card game included with Windows for Workgroups. 
\par \pard\plain \li120\sb80\sl-240 \f25\fs20\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain \s10\fi-270\li360\sl-240 \f25\fs20\lang1033 1.  Start {\b Chat} (and challenge your opponent. Let's call your opponent SPOT. (Chat is one of the Windows for Workgroups Accessories.  It lets network users
 interactively type messages to each other. You do not need Chat to play the game. It justs makes it easier to communicate with your opponent.)
\par \pard \s10\li120\sl-240 
\par \pard \s10\fi-360\li480\sl-240 2.  SPOT starts {\b Net Gomuku} (NETGO.EXE)
\par \pard \s10\li120\sl-240 
\par \pard \s10\fi-270\li360\sl-240 3.  SPOT selects the last radio button labeled "wait for a Net Challenger." and presses the OK button.
\par \pard\plain \s11\li120\sb120\sa120 \f25\fs20\lang1033 \{bml wait.bmp\}
\par \pard\plain \s10\fi-360\li480\sl-240\tx1620 \f25\fs20\lang1033 4.  SPOT tells you via Chat that he is waiting for you to connect.
\par \pard \s10\li120\sl-240 
\par \pard \s10\fi-360\li480\sl-240 5.  You start {\b Net Gomuku}.
\par \pard \s10\li120\sl-240 
\par \pard \s10\fi-360\li480\sl-240 6.  You select the first radio button labeled "NetDDE Player".
\par \pard\plain \s11\li120\sb120\sa120 \f25\fs20\lang1033 \{bml spot.bmp\}
\par \pard\plain \s10\fi-360\li480\sl-240 \f25\fs20\lang1033 7.  You type in the name of SPOT's computer and press the {\b Okay }button.
\par \pard \s10\li120\sl-240 
\par \pard \s10\fi-360\li480\sl-240 8  You wait for {\b Net Gomuku} to connect to SPOT's computer.
\par \pard \s10\li120\sl-240 
\par \pard \s10\fi-360\li480\sl-240 9  Start placing your pegs....
